  <head>
    <meta http-equiv="CACHE-CONTROL" name="CACHE-CONTROL" CONTENT="NO-CACHE"/>    
    <meta http-equiv="PRAGMA" name="PRAGMA" CONTENT="NO-CACHE"/>     
    <META HTTP-EQUIV="EXPIRES" CONTENT="0"/>        
  </head>  
  <body>
    <section name="Field Exclusion">
      <subsection name="Excluding Fields">
         <p>Dozer supports excluding fields from a mapping using the field-exclude tag. We also
         support field excludes going one-way as shown in the example.</p>
         <source>
           <![CDATA[ 
<field-exclude> 
  <a>fieldToExclude</a> 
  <b>fieldToExclude</b> 
</field-exclude>           

<field-exclude type="one-way""> 
  <a>fieldToExclude</a> 
  <b>fieldToExclude</b> 
</field-exclude>           
            ]]>
          </source>
      </subsection>        
    </section>
  </body>
</document>